</mei>
<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key G, 4/4. LH "33" triads throughout, RH parallel thirds.
- Bars 1-4 = verse 1; bars 5-8 = verse 2 (variation in RH voicing choices).
- Bridge bars 7-8: secondary dominants D/F# and A7 for tension.
- Final bars 9-12: Em→D→G cadence, LH ascends from E2 to D2.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH common tone D3 sustained from D to F#° chords.
- RH counterpoint descends G→E in bars 11-12 against ascending melody.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bright open bars 1-4; richer 7th voicings bars 7-10 (bridge); decisive final V7-I cadence.
-->
